# GitHub issues (andyburdick72/lego_inventory)

Use the **GitHub CLI** with the **andyburdick72** account. Do not use `andy-cleverlawn` here.

- When the user references an issue by **number** or URL, run:

  `gh issue view <N> --repo andyburdick72/lego_inventory --json title,body,state,labels,assignees,milestone,url,projectItems`

  Add **`comments`** only when the thread matters.

- Prefer **`--json`** for structured fields. Do not scrape HTML or use anonymous GitHub API.

- **Project #1** (Priority / Size / Status): needs `project` scope (`gh auth refresh -h github.com -s read:project,project` as andyburdick72). If `projectItems` is empty or `gh project` errors, say so — do not invent board state.

- **Never** create `priority:*` / `size:*` labels. Those are project fields.
- **Never** invent new labels; use existing `type:*` / `area:*` / `copilot` only.
